# Application Infra

## Project layout

```text
lib/
├── main.dart                 # ProviderContainer + appStartupProvider + UncontrolledProviderScope
├── app/
│   ├── app.dart              # MaterialApp.router (ConsumerWidget)
│   └── router.dart           # @riverpod GoRouter — aggregates feature routes
├── core/
│   ├── error/                # AppError
│   ├── result/               # Result<T>
│   ├── providers/            # runtime @riverpod (SharedPreferences, Talker)
│   ├── theme/                # AppTheme, ThemeExtensions
│   └── widgets/              # shared UI components (PrimaryButton, etc.)
└── features/
    ├── home/                 # TIC-1 — new game / resume
    ├── game/
    └── settings/             # TIC-8 — AI difficulty

```

Features follow `feature-architecture.mdc`. `core/` holds shared abstractions with no feature imports. `app/` wires router and theme only.

**Single Riverpod root scope** — `UncontrolledProviderScope` declared in `main.dart` only, backed by a `ProviderContainer` initialized at startup. `App` is a `ConsumerWidget` with `MaterialApp.router`, no nested scope.

## Target stack

| Package | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `flutter_riverpod` + `riverpod_annotation` | DI + state |
| `riverpod_generator` (dev) | `@riverpod` codegen |
| `go_router` | Navigation |
| `freezed` + `freezed_annotation` | Immutable entities / UI states |
| `json_serializable` + `json_annotation` | DTO serialization (data layer) |
| `build_runner` (dev) | Code generation |
| `shared_preferences` | Game persistence (TIC-7) |
| `talker` | Logging (never `print()`) |
| `mockito` (dev) | Test mocks — `when` / `verify` on domain abstractions |

## Bootstrap (`main.dart`)

- `WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized()` before any async init
- `ProviderContainer` created in `main()`, async startup awaited **before** `runApp`
- `appStartupProvider` (`core/providers/app_startup_provider.dart`) initializes runtime dependencies (e.g. `SharedPreferences`)
- `UncontrolledProviderScope` passes the pre-initialized container to the widget tree
- Tests override providers via `ProviderScope(overrides: [...])` or `ProviderContainer.test()` — they do not call `main()`

```dart
Future<void> main() async {
  WidgetsFlutterBinding.ensureInitialized();

  final container = ProviderContainer();
  await container.read(appStartupProvider.future);

  runApp(UncontrolledProviderScope(
    container: container,
    child: const App(),
  ));
}
```

## Router (`app/router.dart`)

`GoRouter` exposed as a codegen provider, aggregating routes from each feature:

```dart
@riverpod
GoRouter router(Ref ref) {
  return GoRouter(
    initialLocation: HomeRoutes.path,
    routes: [
      ...homeRoutes,
      ...gameRoutes,
      ...settingsRoutes,
    ],
  );
}

```

`App` consumes it:

```dart
class App extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    return MaterialApp.router(
      routerConfig: ref.watch(routerProvider),
      theme: buildAppTheme(),
    );
  }
}
```

Features expose route lists from `navigation/<feature>_routes.dart`. No feature imports another feature's internal paths.

## Persistence

| Service | Where initialized | Access from features |
| --- | --- | --- |
| SharedPreferences | initialized in `appStartupProvider`, exposed via `sharedPreferencesProvider` | Repository abstraction in `domain/repositories/` only |

## Logging (Talker)

`Talker` instance provided via `@riverpod` in `core/providers/talker_provider.dart`, injected into repositories via `di/` — never `ref.read` inside a repository.

Use for non-UI diagnostic logging only — never `print()`. Repositories log persistence failures; Notifiers do not log business outcomes.

```dart
@riverpod
Talker talker(Ref ref) => Talker();

// di/game_repository_provider.dart — inject via constructor
@riverpod
GameRepository gameRepository(Ref ref) {
  return LocalGameRepository(
    dataSource: ref.watch(gameLocalDataSourceProvider),
    talker: ref.watch(talkerProvider),
  );
}

```

## Theme (`core/theme/`)

See `design-system.mdc` for ThemeExtension usage. Never hardcode colors or text styles in widgets.

## Generated files — never edit by hand

- `*.g.dart`, `*.freezed.dart` — regenerate via `dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs`

## Secrets and config

Local game, no external API. If config is needed: `AppConfig` or `--dart-define`, never hardcoded. Never read or expose secrets from config files.

## flutter_hooks

Used with `hooks_riverpod` for view-level lifecycle and local UI state.

- **Riverpod Notifiers** → app / business state
- **Hooks** → route visibility, animations, `TextEditingController`, `ScrollController`, etc.
- Shared hooks → `lib/core/hooks/`
